Title: Avoid launching the desktop MIME type editor on iOS

## Problem

`KMimeTypeEditor::editMimeType()` launches the external `keditfiletype`
executable with `QProcess::startDetached()`.

iOS applications cannot launch arbitrary external processes, Qt for iOS does
not provide this process-launching operation, and `keditfiletype` is not
available in an iOS application bundle. The call therefore prevents
KWidgetsAddons from compiling for iOS and cannot provide meaningful behavior
at runtime.

## Proposed change

On iOS, replace the external process launch with a modal error message stating
that MIME type editing is unsupported. Keep the existing `keditfiletype`
behavior on all other platforms.

## Impact

Applications can continue calling the API on iOS and receive a clear user-facing
result instead of an unavailable desktop workflow. Other platforms are
unaffected.

